modules.description: Compares two instances of type `t` using a three-way comparison, returning -1, 0, or 1 based on their relative ordering. It is designed for use with ordered data structures that require custom comparison logic. This function is essential for sorting or determining equality in contexts where default comparisons are insufficient.

Calculates differences between two strings using a line-based algorithm, producing a list of edit operations. It processes strings and returns a structured representation of additions, deletions, and unchanged sections. This is useful for implementing version control features or tracking changes in text documents.

Computes differences between two arrays of items, producing a list of change records. Each record indicates additions, deletions, or no change at specific positions. Used to track line-by-line or character-by-character modifications in text comparison.
